      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LOCHINVAR HUMMER (6) thrives over the longer races. Was too tough when scoring last time over 600m at The Meadows in a Grade 4/5 (34.28). Has a strong winning record here at the trip including two wins. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Great chance to get the job done again. ZAMBORA BLISS (2) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot before finishing second (29.56) and beaten 4 lengths over 515m at this track. Expected to be in the finish again. PAW VINCE (4) turned spotting a big start finishing eighth (35.40) last time in a Grade 4/5 at The Meadows. Solid record at the distance winning six races. Leading chance. MOONLIGHT MILLER (8) can find the frame without surprising.",
